			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hey I recently turned 60 and after screaming like a little girl, jumping about joyously, urinating on myself and all sorts of other fun things, I scribed my new spells.
<br />

<br />
I particularly wanted to test Savagery so I cast it and it gave me the message indicating that I needed a peridot reagent.  Ok, fine.  Bought up a bunch of those to store up as this was a spell I knew I would be using all the time.
<br />

<br />
Then I cast it and wow! 450 mana a pop.  Whew!  Oh well, assload of mana and a peridot notwithstanding, it still looked like an awesome spell.  I loaded Frenzy and cast it. and WOOT it stacks with Savagery!  I was in hog heaven.  I was sitting there admiring all my increased stats and imagining the amount of ass I could kick with this combination when I looked up at the buff slots.
<br />

<br />
The Savagery icon was blinking.
<br />

<br />
WTF?
<br />

<br />
450 mana, takes FOREVER to refresh, costs a peridot to cast and it lasts barely long enough for me to load and cast Frenzy and look at my stats???  Geez, talk about a let down.  You would think with the high mana cost and the reagent requirement it would last longer than I would in bed with Cameron Diaz.
<br />

<br />
Geez.  
<br />

<br />
/rant off<br />_________________<br />Baron Judor Petdetective -- 61 Barbarian Savage Lord and Humpleg the Faithful Wolf
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=785455" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=785455</a>
<br />

