				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">[quote]Grats, you win the stupid question of the day award![/quote]
<br />

<br />
Be nice, now.  Not everyone has experienced the lubbin known as Ferocity.
<br />

<br />
Ferocity adds 65 to all of your resists.  It also adds 150 (200ish with the melee bonus to atk buffs) to you attack.  The higher attack makes you do more damage over time.  Yes, it is 600 mana.  But with KEI/C4/C5+ SD+ FT items you can easily  keep it going on you, and at least one groupmate.
<br />

<br />
It doesn't cost you that full bubble of mana once you get 250+ wis, and it lasts longer than 6.5 minutes with Extended Enhancement and Spell Casting Reinforcement.  With a 15% EEIV item and SCR3 it will last 9.5 minutes.  As to the long refresh, if you are complaining about it eating so much mana, why would you want to cast it more often?  It is a 2 minute refresh, which gives you time to regen some mana to spread out the load.
<br />

<br />
I can't see where you claim it doesn't last a whole fight /boggle.
<br />

<br />
In a group, even if you do not cast it on yourself, keep it on the rogue/ranger and it will increase their damage output quite nicely.  That 600 mana is one of the best things you can do to keep the group going.
<br />

<br />
As to it costing 20k, that is your server.  On BB you can find it for 8kish if you are patient.  I paid 12k for mine, and do not regret it.  
<br />

<br />
Nihtrog
<br />
65 Beastlord BB</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
