				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I agree; Savagery is a pretty disappointing spell.  It's not suppose to be the end-all be-all, but in it's current state it's pretty worthless.
<br />

<br />
On the other hand, I simply can not understand how anyone could think Fero is not worth getting.  It's Savagery without the component and better stats.  The need of a peridot is why Savagery is worthless; it gets VERY expensive to keep it up.  Fero is not that mana entensive in most groups if you have any form of KEI and in some situations it's about the only way to increase the DPS you're helping to put out through spells.  Water in BoT comes to mind since they resist out nukes and poison based DoT's.  
<br />

<br />
That said, I don't always use Fero in groups because I can do better DPS through nukes.  On a raid, however, where mana regen is ridiculous thanks to VoQ/Pot9/SD/Bard song, I can keep it on 3 people and nuke every mob we pull.  It's really a great spell to help the main tank resist EP boss AE's too.<br />_________________<br /><b>"They call me the king of sticks.  Perhaps you've heard of me."</b>
